# Bass Guitar Implementation & Jam Session Fixes — Walkthrough

## 🎸 Bass Guitar Mode Added

I have successfully built and integrated the complete Bass Guitar mode you requested, matching your exact specifications.

### How to Play the Bass Guitar

1. **Plucking (Right Hand)**: Hold your right index finger up so the camera sees it. Move it up and down across the four strings (`E2`, `A2`, `D2`, `G2`). A rapid downward or upward motion (a "flick") simulating a pluck will trigger the bass sound.
2. **Fretting (Left Hand)**: Hold your left wrist/hand up to the camera. The position of your left hand horizontally across the screen determines the "fret" you are holding.
   - Far left: Open String (0 semitones)
   - Moving right: 1st fret (+2 semitones)
   - Further right: 2nd fret (+4 semitones)
   - And so on up to the 4th fret (+7 semitones).
3. **Audio Feedback**: The application now loads the actual [.wav](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/Bass%20sounds/g-bass.wav) files from your `bass sounds/` folder ([e2-bass.wav](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/Bass%20sounds/e2-bass.wav), [a2-bass.wav](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/Bass%20sounds/a2-bass.wav), [d-bass.wav](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/Bass%20sounds/d-bass.wav), [g-bass.wav](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/Bass%20sounds/g-bass.wav)), and pitches them up dynamically in Python based on your left hand's fret position!
4. **Visual Feedback**:
   - When you pluck, the specific string will flash white and visually "wobble" like a real string vibrating.
   - The desktop UI string status panel on the left will highlight which string was plucked and track how long ago it happened.
   - The fret control panel on the right will smoothly animate a bar to show exactly which fret the camera thinks your left hand is holding.

